Smørrebrød is the Danish term for "open faced sandwich".  It typically has meat, fish or vegetables and is decorated with things like herbs, lemon, aspic, egg, and mayonnaise.  Smørrebrød is often also referred to as smorgasbord which is Sweedish for a buffet that includes open faced sandwiches.  The Danish smorgasbord is traditional lunch-fare and in December figures largely in Christmas lunches.